01:02:39,559 --> 01:02:43,010
When this is over, if he wants
my badge, he can have that too.

489
01:02:45,064 --> 01:02:47,769
You wouldn't have a belt of booze
around here, would you?

490
01:02:54,867 --> 01:02:56,941
Lieutenant Bressler's office.

491
01:02:59,830 --> 01:03:01,869
- Put him on.
- What is it?

492
01:03:02,541 --> 01:03:07,748
It's Park Emergency. They just treated
a guy who had a knife wound in the leg.

493
01:03:09,506 --> 01:03:12,507
Yeah, Doctor?
What'd this guy look like?

494
01:03:13,051 --> 01:03:14,878
Long blond hair...

495
01:03:15,137 --> 01:03:18,091
...medium build, about 150 pounds.

496
01:03:18,724 --> 01:03:19,921
Pale complexion.

497
01:03:20,183 --> 01:03:23,766
- He didn't give you his name, Doc?
- Nope.

498
01:03:24,897 --> 01:03:26,605
They usually give a phony name.

499
01:03:28,067 --> 01:03:30,060
But I've seen him someplace.

500
01:03:30,611 --> 01:03:34,739
It's important you remember. There's
a 14-year-old girl who's suffocating.

501
01:03:34,990 --> 01:03:36,983
I'm trying to think!

502
01:03:37,243 --> 01:03:38,618
It was...

503
01:03:39,412 --> 01:03:41,120
I believe he works around here.

504
01:03:41,331 --> 01:03:44,414
Doctor, could you give
him something? He's in pain!

505
01:03:44,667 --> 01:03:46,327
Yes, just a moment.

506
01:03:50,590 --> 01:03:52,049
She'll be dead in an hour!

507
01:03:52,300 --> 01:03:54,340
I'm trying to remember!

508
01:03:56,721 --> 01:03:58,630
I've got who he is.

509
01:03:59,474 --> 01:04:03,721
When they had football,
he used to sell programs at the stadium.

510
01:04:04,354 --> 01:04:07,058
I think the groundskeeper
lets him live there.

511
01:04:07,315 --> 01:04:09,985
- Live where?
- There.

512
01:04:14,990 --> 01:04:16,615
Kezar Stadium.

513
01:05:21,099 --> 01:05:23,223
Illegal entry. No warrant.

514
01:05:23,560 --> 01:05:25,304
Looks like we climb.

515
01:05:26,689 --> 01:05:28,183
Too much linguine.

516
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:32,108
I'll find another way.

517
01:08:49,230 --> 01:08:50,260
Stop!

518
01:09:10,210 --> 01:09:13,414
Don't do anything more!
You tried to kill me!

519
01:09:14,797 --> 01:09:15,960
You need any help?

520
01:09:17,426 --> 01:09:21,554
- Go on and get some air, fatso.
- Please! No more!

521
01:09:21,972 --> 01:09:25,506
Can't you see I'm hurt?
You shot me! Please, don't!

522
01:09:26,059 --> 01:09:28,217
Let me have a doctor!

523
01:09:28,478 --> 01:09:31,017
Please, get me the doctor!
Don't kill me!

524
01:09:31,565 --> 01:09:33,143
The girl, where is she?

525
01:09:33,400 --> 01:09:34,563
You tried to kill me!

526
01:09:34,819 --> 01:09:38,981
If I did, your head would be splattered
all over this field. Where's the girl?

527
01:09:39,239 --> 01:09:40,402
I want a lawyer.

528
01:09:40,616 --> 01:09:42,525
I said, where's the girl?

529
01:09:42,869 --> 01:09:46,035
- I have the right for one.
- Where's the girl?

530
01:09:47,290 --> 01:09:49,531
I have the right to a lawyer!

531
01:09:50,500 --> 01:09:51,960
Don't! Please!

532
01:09:52,211 --> 01:09:54,749
I have rights. I want a lawyer!

533
01:11:33,274 --> 01:11:35,598
Harry Callahan.
He said it was urgent.

534
01:11:35,859 --> 01:11:39,857
Yes, the district attorney has
been wanting to talk to you.

535
01:11:40,155 --> 01:11:43,359
<i>- It's Inspector Callahan.
- Have him come in, please.</i>

536
01:11:44,410 --> 01:11:46,617
Won't you come this way?

537
01:11:47,038 --> 01:11:50,453
- May I bring you in a cup of coffee?
- No, thanks.

538
01:11:59,133 --> 01:12:00,925
I'll be done in a minute.

539
01:12:01,677 --> 01:12:03,052
Have a seat.

540
01:12:07,475 --> 01:12:10,974
I've just been looking over
your arrest report.

541
01:12:12,564 --> 01:12:15,933
A very unusual piece of police work.

542
01:12:17,694 --> 01:12:18,975
Really amazing.

543
01:12:20,239 --> 01:12:21,483
I had some luck.

544
01:12:21,740 --> 01:12:25,524
You're lucky I'm not indicting you for
assault with intent to commit murder!

545
01:12:29,248 --> 01:12:33,293
Where does it say you've got a right
to kick down doors, torture suspects?

546
01:12:33,544 --> 01:12:37,494
Deny medical attention and legal
counsel? Where have you been?

547
01:12:38,257 --> 01:12:40,962
Does Escobedo ring a bell?
Miranda?

548
01:12:42,762 --> 01:12:45,679
You must have heard
of the 4th Amendment!

549
01:12:47,098 --> 01:12:49,969
What I'm saying is,
that man had rights.

550
01:12:51,354 --> 01:12:54,225
I'm all broken up
about that man's rights.

551
01:12:54,440 --> 01:12:56,765
You should be.
I've got news for you.

552
01:12:56,985 --> 01:12:59,689
When he's well enough
to leave the hospital, he walks.

553
01:13:01,030 --> 01:13:02,524
What are you talking about?

554
01:13:02,782 --> 01:13:03,945
He's free!

555
01:13:04,784 --> 01:13:06,159
You're letting him go?

556
01:13:06,411 --> 01:13:08,203
We have to.
We can't try him.

557
01:13:08,455 --> 01:13:09,700
And why is that?

558
01:13:09,955 --> 01:13:12,957
Because I'm not wasting
1/2 million tax dollars...

559
01:13:13,209 --> 01:13:15,451
...on a trial we can't possibly win.

560
01:13:15,920 --> 01:13:18,459
The problem is,
we don't have any evidence.

561
01:13:18,799 --> 01:13:21,586
- What do you call that?
- I call it nothing.

562
01:13:22,051 --> 01:13:23,249
Zero.

563
01:13:24,679 --> 01:13:28,464
You're saying that Ballistics can't
match the bullet up to this rifle?

564
01:13:28,725 --> 01:13:31,726
It does not matter
what Ballistics can do!

565
01:13:32,146 --> 01:13:35,016
This rifle might make a nice souvenir.

566
01:13:36,107 --> 01:13:38,681
- But it's inadmissible as evidence!
- Who says?

567
01:13:38,944 --> 01:13:40,107
It's the law.

568
01:13:40,863 --> 01:13:42,322
Then the law is crazy!

569
01:13:43,408 --> 01:13:46,324
This is Judge Bannerman
of the appellate court.

570
01:13:46,535 --> 01:13:51,411
He holds classes in constitutional
law. I've asked him for an opinion.

571
01:13:51,666 --> 01:13:52,745
Your Honor?

572
01:13:54,044 --> 01:13:58,871
In my opinion, the search
of the suspect's quarters was illegal.

573
01:13:59,089 --> 01:14:03,302
Evidence obtained thereby, such as
that hunting rifle for instance...

574
01:14:03,511 --> 01:14:05,420
...is inadmissible in court.

575
01:14:05,680 --> 01:14:09,629
You should have gotten
a search warrant. I'm sorry.

576
01:14:09,850 --> 01:14:13,136
- It's that simple.
- Search warrant? A girl was dying!

577
01:14:13,354 --> 01:14:16,439
She was, in fact, dead
according to the medical report!

578
01:14:16,691 --> 01:14:17,854
But I didn't know that!

579
01:14:18,443 --> 01:14:23,271
The court would recognize the officer's
legitimate concern for the girl...

580
01:14:23,573 --> 01:14:27,737
...but there is no way they can
possibly condone police torture.

581
01:14:28,453 --> 01:14:32,037
All evidence concerning the girl,
the suspect's confession...

582
01:14:32,291 --> 01:14:33,535
...physical evidence...

583
01:14:33,750 --> 01:14:36,075
...would have to be excluded.

584
01:14:41,968 --> 01:14:44,044
There must be something
you can get him on!

585
01:14:44,262 --> 01:14:47,262
Without the evidence
of the gun and the girl?

586
01:14:48,057 --> 01:14:50,809
I couldn't convict him
of spitting on the sidewalk!

587
01:14:52,520 --> 01:14:54,927
Now, the suspect's rights...

588
01:14:55,190 --> 01:14:56,980
...were violated...

589
01:14:57,232 --> 01:14:59,391
...under the 4th and 5th...

590
01:14:59,652 --> 01:15:02,439
...and probably the 6th
and 14th Amendments.

591
01:15:02,697 --> 01:15:05,235
And Ann Mary Deacon,
what about her rights?

592
01:15:05,491 --> 01:15:08,576
She's raped and left in a hole to die!
Who speaks for her?

593
01:15:08,827 --> 01:15:10,370
The district attorney's office!

594
01:15:11,372 --> 01:15:13,080
If you'll let us.

595
01:15:14,751 --> 01:15:18,831
I have a wife and 3 kids. I don't want
him on the streets any more than you do.

596
01:15:19,172 --> 01:15:20,915
He won't be out there long.

597
01:15:21,174 --> 01:15:23,332
What is that supposed to mean?

598
01:15:23,801 --> 01:15:26,803
Sooner or later he will stub his toe
and I'll be there.

599
01:15:27,013 --> 01:15:29,719
This office won't stand
for any harassment!

600
01:15:30,392 --> 01:15:34,639
You're crazy if you think you've heard
the last of him. He will kill again.

601
01:15:35,022 --> 01:15:36,515
How do you know?

602
01:15:37,816 --> 01:15:39,560
Because he likes it.

603
01:18:07,094 --> 01:18:08,838
You sure you weren't tailed?

604
01:18:09,388 --> 01:18:10,587
Yeah.

605
01:18:35,290 --> 01:18:37,532
You really want $200 worth.

606
01:18:38,628 --> 01:18:40,537
Every penny of it.

607
01:18:54,851 --> 01:18:56,310
Might as well be comfortable.

608
01:18:57,020 --> 01:18:58,646
Go on, sit.

609
01:19:06,364 --> 01:19:07,857
Relax.

610
01:19:09,075 --> 01:19:11,032
Take it easy.

611
01:19:11,410 --> 01:19:13,736
It's going to be all right.

612
01:19:55,081 --> 01:19:57,322
You sure you want the rest of it?

613
01:19:58,084 --> 01:19:59,827
Every penny's worth!

614
01:20:01,378 --> 01:20:04,829
You black son of a bitch!

615
01:20:26,530 --> 01:20:28,985
This one's on the house.

616
01:20:43,588 --> 01:20:45,166
That's got to be him.

617
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:51,887
Are you claiming that the
San Francisco Police did this to you?

618
01:20:52,139 --> 01:20:54,048
I swear it. As God is my judge.

619
01:20:54,308 --> 01:20:56,431
Why are they harassing you?

620
01:20:56,685 --> 01:20:58,678
They tried to frame me with the murder.

621
01:20:58,938 --> 01:21:01,809
And now they're trying to murder me.
And look at me!

622
01:21:02,066 --> 01:21:06,230
I'm innocent until proven guilty
and look at what they did to me.

623
01:21:06,528 --> 01:21:09,696
Everywhere I go cops follow me.
And just look at me!

624
01:21:10,283 --> 01:21:13,237
Just a minute, nurse.
Let me ask him one more question.

625
01:21:13,453 --> 01:21:15,492
Did you see who did this to you?

626
01:21:15,746 --> 01:21:16,909
Can you identify him?

627
01:21:17,206 --> 01:21:21,785
<i>His name is Callahan. He's a big cop.
Works Homicide. Callahan.</i>

628
01:21:24,256 --> 01:21:27,375
Now, that's the rerun
from the 4 o'clock news.

629
01:21:27,633 --> 01:21:30,588
<i>Since then he's given
a statement to The Chronicle.</i>

630
01:21:31,096 --> 01:21:34,381
He claims you've been following him.
And beat him up.

631
01:21:35,350 --> 01:21:37,142
What about it, Harry?

632
01:21:38,062 --> 01:21:40,552
- You want my star?
- I want an answer.

633
01:21:40,814 --> 01:21:42,557
Have you been following him?

634
01:21:44,192 --> 01:21:47,692
Yeah, I've been following him
on my own time.

635
01:21:48,113 --> 01:21:50,354
- Anybody can tell I didn't do that.
- How?

636
01:21:50,907 --> 01:21:53,825
Because he looks
too damn good, that's how!

637
01:21:54,620 --> 01:21:57,289
Before I let you go,
let's get one thing straight.

638
01:21:57,539 --> 01:22:00,245
I don't want any more surveillance!

639
01:22:01,211 --> 01:22:02,953
Neither does he.

640
01:22:04,922 --> 01:22:06,001
What does that mean?

641
01:22:07,800 --> 01:22:09,425
Good night, sir.

642
01:22:13,306 --> 01:22:15,049
Go ahead. Try them.

643
01:22:15,599 --> 01:22:19,183
- Guy makes them where I always eat.
- Thank you.

644
01:22:19,437 --> 01:22:22,107
I talked to Bressler
about being on with me.

645
01:22:23,107 --> 01:22:25,776
So you know you got a spot
when you get out.

646
01:22:26,444 --> 01:22:29,528
I don't know
if I am coming back, Harry.

647
01:22:32,701 --> 01:22:35,821
Doing a lot of thinking
about it and...

648
01:22:37,831 --> 01:22:41,116
I have a teaching credential.
And I figure...

649
01:22:41,835 --> 01:22:43,828
...what for? You know?

650
01:22:47,216 --> 01:22:50,133
- Time for therapy.
- You hang in there now.

651
01:22:56,142 --> 01:22:58,300
See you tomorrow. Same time?

652
01:23:21,168 --> 01:23:23,919
- It's my fault, you know.
- What?

653
01:23:24,545 --> 01:23:26,917
His leaving.
I thought I could take it.

654
01:23:27,173 --> 01:23:28,667
No class.

655
01:23:29,426 --> 01:23:31,632
- Don't ever say that.
- What?

656
01:23:31,886 --> 01:23:33,761
Don't ever low-rate yourself.

657
01:23:34,348 --> 01:23:38,012
What I meant was, whatever it takes
to be a cop's wife...

658
01:23:38,268 --> 01:23:40,308
...I'm just not sure I'm making it.

659
01:23:40,562 --> 01:23:43,100
He really tries,
and all these bastards...

660
01:23:43,356 --> 01:23:45,682
..."pig" this and "pig" that.

661
01:23:46,902 --> 01:23:50,685
But maybe it's when I watch him
walk out that door at night.

662
01:23:50,948 --> 01:23:52,192
And I think...

663
01:23:53,367 --> 01:23:55,822
...what if it's the last time
I see him?

664
01:23:56,912 --> 01:23:58,572
Am I the only one?

665
01:23:58,873 --> 01:24:00,829
Doesn't it drive your wife crazy?

666
01:24:01,124 --> 01:24:02,239
No.

667
01:24:03,377 --> 01:24:05,535
You mean she got used to it?

668
01:24:06,047 --> 01:24:07,838
No, she never did, really.

669
01:24:08,090 --> 01:24:09,371
What, then?

670
01:24:10,093 --> 01:24:11,635
She's dead.

671
01:24:12,386 --> 01:24:14,130
Please, forgive me.

672
01:24:14,805 --> 01:24:18,009
She was driving home
and a drunk crossed the center line.

673
01:24:18,268 --> 01:24:19,727
No reason for it, really.

674
01:24:20,603 --> 01:24:22,845
- I'm so sorry.
- That's okay.

675
01:24:23,605 --> 01:24:25,266
I want you to tell Chico...

676
01:24:26,150 --> 01:24:28,357
...that I understand him quitting.

677
01:24:28,612 --> 01:24:31,779
I think he's right.
This is no life for you two.

678
01:24:32,407 --> 01:24:35,573
- Why do you stay in it, then?
- I don't know.

679
01:24:37,203 --> 01:24:38,614
I really don't.

680
01:25:15,910 --> 01:25:18,152
Let me have a fifth of Seagram's.
Please.

681
01:25:19,622 --> 01:25:21,532
What the hell happened to you?

682
01:25:21,792 --> 01:25:23,748
My wife's brother.

683
01:25:24,001 --> 01:25:25,116
I hit her...

684
01:25:25,377 --> 01:25:27,038
...so he hit me.

685
01:25:27,297 --> 01:25:28,791
Several times.

686
01:25:30,341 --> 01:25:31,800
$5.69.

687
01:25:33,804 --> 01:25:36,887
You're the guy
that's been robbed all these times.

688
01:25:37,140 --> 01:25:39,596
14 times the last 3 years.

689
01:25:39,851 --> 01:25:42,853
Last 2 times, I sent them
out of here on platters.

690
01:25:43,105 --> 01:25:45,679
I'm getting to be a pretty good shot.

691
01:25:46,816 --> 01:25:50,648
And I always keep it right here.
Right where it's handy.

692
01:25:50,863 --> 01:25:53,354
Please, I scare easy.

693
01:25:56,618 --> 01:25:59,323
Dirty son of a bitch! You pilferer!

694
01:26:35,825 --> 01:26:36,987
Goodbye.

695
01:26:38,286 --> 01:26:40,078
See you tomorrow.

696
01:26:50,006 --> 01:26:52,711
Everybody out who gets out here?

697
01:26:53,052 --> 01:26:54,629
School bus inspector.

698
01:26:54,845 --> 01:26:57,466
One minute.
I'm not allowed to have anybody...

699
01:26:57,681 --> 01:26:59,305
I'm authorizing it, so go.

700
01:26:59,599 --> 01:27:01,391
What are you doing?
I don't know you.

701
01:27:01,643 --> 01:27:05,938
Hear me, old hag. Drive or I'll
decorate this bus with your brains.

702
01:27:08,026 --> 01:27:11,643
- Where?
- Just get started. I'll tell you where.

703
01:27:16,409 --> 01:27:17,951
Let's have some fun now.

704
01:27:18,327 --> 01:27:19,738
Who knows a song?

705
01:27:19,913 --> 01:27:22,996
Everybody knows a song. You?
You must know a beautiful one.

706
01:27:23,457 --> 01:27:25,284
Come on, sing for us.

707
01:29:08,649 --> 01:29:12,563
- Millie, this is Inspector Callahan.
- The Mayor is waiting for you.

708
01:29:16,866 --> 01:29:19,439
- What's up?
- Another note from our boy.

709
01:29:19,702 --> 01:29:23,830
- Who's he grabbed now?
- That's the trouble, we don't know yet.

710
01:29:26,000 --> 01:29:28,788
The jet must be fueled and
ready to go in half an hour.

711
01:29:29,338 --> 01:29:32,337
Skeleton crew.
They must be volunteers.

712
01:29:32,923 --> 01:29:34,798
Tell them the man is dangerous.

713
01:29:35,051 --> 01:29:38,836
I'll read you this note which
was delivered at 8:00 this morning.

714
01:29:39,181 --> 01:29:40,592
"To the City of San Francisco.

715
01:29:40,808 --> 01:29:43,345
You double-crossed me
for the last time.

716
01:29:43,601 --> 01:29:48,310
I'm warning you to have my $200,000
in a jet airplane ready and waiting.

717
01:29:49,065 --> 01:29:52,814
I'll call the Mayor's office at 1:00
and tell you about the hostages...

718
01:29:53,070 --> 01:29:55,643
...who I will be happy to kill
if you don't do...

719
01:29:55,905 --> 01:29:58,278
...exactly what I say. Scorpio."

720
01:30:01,245 --> 01:30:03,321
Better have somebody standing by!

721
01:30:03,581 --> 01:30:05,490
I don't think it's a false alarm.

722
01:30:05,708 --> 01:30:07,949
<i>There's a call for you on line 2.</i>

723
01:30:08,168 --> 01:30:10,624
<i>I think it's the one
you've been waiting for.</i>

724
01:30:17,262 --> 01:30:20,131
<i>- It's the Mayor.
- I got 7 kids from Park Street School.</i>

725
01:30:22,642 --> 01:30:23,840
I got the bus and...

726
01:30:24,101 --> 01:30:27,601
Come on, honey, now back in the bus.
That's a good girl.

727
01:30:27,855 --> 01:30:29,683
I got the bus driver.
Here she is.

728
01:30:30,066 --> 01:30:31,477
Just tell him.

729
01:30:31,943 --> 01:30:33,402
Not my fault, he had a gun...

730
01:30:33,611 --> 01:30:34,525
Just your name!

731
01:30:38,575 --> 01:30:40,034
<i>This is Marcella Platt.</i>

732
01:30:41,911 --> 01:30:44,449
<i>You can check if you want.
But I don 't see any point.</i>

733
01:30:44,706 --> 01:30:46,248
<i>I'm not bullshitting.</i>

734
01:30:46,458 --> 01:30:49,578
<i>It's simple. I got the kids.
You start screwing around...</i>

735
01:30:49,794 --> 01:30:51,373
<i>... the kids start dying.</i>

736
01:30:51,589 --> 01:30:55,206
<i>- The plane ready?
